	volume = {69},
	url = {http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/S0920-3796(03)00113-3},
	abstract = {The recently developed Intermediate Energy Activation File {IEAF-2001} and the inventory activation code Analytic and Laplacian Adaptive Radioactivity Analysis ({ALARA)} have been tested in a computational benchmark with a D-T fusion neutron spectrum against the European Activation System {EASY-2001}, extensively used below 20 {MeV}, and in an integral activation experiment with a d-Li ({IFMIF)} neutron spectrum. Agreement in general is good. The suitability of {IEAF-2001} library for activation analyses in the energy domain up to 55 {MeV} was demonstrated with the need for improvements of some specific cross sections. Application of {ALARA/IEAF-2001} to a comparative study of activation and transmutation processes in Eurofer steel irradiated in the {IFMIF} high flux test module and in a fusion Demo reactor first wall has shown their general similarity, the specific quantitative differences being caused by the higher neutron energies produced in {IFMIF.} \&copy; 2003 Elsevier Science {B.V.} All rights reserved.},
